{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Task\/runInThread(taskFunc:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"runInThread"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"taskFunc"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GTaskThreadFunc","text":"GTaskThreadFunc"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This takes a ref on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"type":"text","text":" until the task completes."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for more details about how "},{"code":"taskFunc","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is handled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Although GLib currently rate-limits the tasks queued via","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_task_run_in_thread()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you should not assume that it will always"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"do this. If you have a very large number of tasks to run (several tens of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tasks), but don’t want them to all run at once, you should only queue a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"limited number of them (around ten) at a time."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be aware that if your task depends on other tasks to complete, use of this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"function could lead to a livelock if the other tasks also use this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and enough of them (around 10) execute in a dependency chain, as that will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exhaust the thread pool. If this situation is possible, consider using a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"separate worker thread or thread pool explicitly, rather than using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_task_run_in_thread()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Runs "},{"code":"taskFunc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in another thread. When ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"taskFunc"},{"type":"text","text":" returns, "},{"code":"task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncReadyCallback","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will be invoked in "},{"code":"task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s [MainContext](\/\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/task\/runinthread(taskfunc:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Task","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Task\/TaskProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"title":"runInThread(taskFunc:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"runInThread"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"taskFunc"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GTaskThreadFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GTaskThreadFunc"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO12TaskProtocolPAAE11runInThread8taskFuncyySpySo6_GTaskVGSg_SvSgAJSpySo13_GCa